## High-Level Policy

After pre-training, the low-level policy 𝜋 (a|s, z) can be applied to downstream tasks by training a task-specific high-level policy 𝜔 (z|s, g), which receives as input the state of the character s and a task-specific goal g, then outputs a latent z for directing the lowlevel policy.

